@page
@model Webority.Web.GovIndia.Pages.Services.LegacyModernizationModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Legacy System Modernisation for Government India";
    ViewData["Description"] = "CMMI Level 5 legacy system modernisation for Indian government — zero-downtime Analyse → Isolate → Migrate → Validate migration to NIC / MeghRaj with full data integrity.";
    ViewData["ActiveNav"] = "services";
    ViewData["BodyClass"] = "services-page";
}
<!-- Hero -->
  <section class="egov-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="egov-hero-content">
        <h1>Legacy System Modernisation for Government India</h1>
        <p class="egov-hero-lead">India’s CMMI Level 5-certified specialist in legacy modernisation — migrating and re-engineering outdated government IT without disrupting live citizen services, with a proven Analyse → Isolate → Migrate → Validate methodology, zero downtime, full data integrity, and NIC / MeghRaj compatibility from day one.</p>
        <p class="svc-hero-standards">Zero Downtime Methodology   ·   Full Data Integrity Validated   ·   NIC &amp; MeghRaj GI Cloud Compatible   ·   STQC-Aligned Testing</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What We Deliver -->
  <section class="egov-band">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="egov-band-grid">
        <div>
          <span class="egov-eyebrow">What We Deliver</span>
          <h2 class="egov-h2">Upgrading Without Switching Off</h2>
          <p class="copy">A significant portion of India’s government IT runs on technology that is 10–20 years old — legacy codebases built for desktop environments, siloed databases that cannot integrate with India Stack, and applications that cannot scale to citizen-demand volumes. The risk of doing nothing is system failure; the risk of a poorly managed migration is citizen service disruption during transition.</p>
          <p class="copy">Government legacy modernisation is the most risk-intensive service in the public sector IT stack. We built our delivery model around one rule: the live government service must remain operational every single day of the migration. Our Analyse → Isolate → Migrate → Validate methodology was designed specifically for this constraint — not adapted from a commercial migration playbook.</p>
          <ul class="egov-checklist">
            <li><span class="egov-check"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg></span> Legacy re-engineering — monolith to microservices</li>
            <li><span class="egov-check"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg></span> Database migration — full data-integrity validation</li>
            <li><span class="egov-check"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg></span> NIC &amp; MeghRaj GI Cloud migration — sovereign</li>
            <li><span class="egov-check"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg></span> eOffice integration — NIC workflow platforms</li>
            <li><span class="egov-check"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg></span> API development for India Stack — Aadhaar, DigiLocker, UPI</li>
            <li><span class="egov-check"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg></span> Desktop-to-web &amp; mobile — GIGW 3.0 / WCAG 2.1 AA</li>
            <li><span class="egov-check"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg></span> Parallel-run architecture — old system stays live</li>
            <li><span class="egov-check"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg></span> STQC-aligned testing, full UAT &amp; VAPT before cutover</li>
          </ul>
          <div class="egov-btn-row">
            <a asp-page="/Contact" class="btn btn-primary btn-glow btn-md"><span class="btn-glow-label">Discuss Your Requirements</span><svg class="btn-glow-arrow" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M5 12h14"/><path d="M13 6l6 6-6 6"/></svg></a>
            <a asp-page="/CaseStudies" class="btn btn-outline btn-md">View Projects</a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="egov-ref-panel">
          <span class="egov-eyebrow">Reference Projects</span>
          <!-- TODO-WG: each public-sector reference below must have approved public listing before publishing. -->
          <ul class="egov-ref-list">
            <li class="egov-ref-item">
              <span class="egov-ref-logo"><img src="/images/logos/gov/qci.png" alt="Quality Council of India — SAMAR" loading="lazy" /></span>
              <span>
                <p class="egov-ref-name">Quality Council of India — SAMAR</p>
                <p class="egov-ref-proj">Paper-based certification lifecycle digitised end-to-end — online application, multi-level approval, digitally signed certificates, QR-verified public validation</p>
              </span>
            </li>
            <li class="egov-ref-item">
              <span class="egov-ref-logo"><img src="/images/logos/gov/parliament-cafeteria.svg" alt="Parliament of India" loading="lazy" /></span>
              <span>
                <p class="egov-ref-name">Parliament of India</p>
                <p class="egov-ref-proj">Sansad Cafeteria — legacy manual processes replaced with integrated digital workflow on parliamentary infrastructure</p>
              </span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Capabilities -->
  <section class="egov-build">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="egov-build-head">
        <span class="egov-eyebrow">Capabilities</span>
        <h2 class="egov-h2">What We Modernise — And How</h2>
        <p>Every modernisation engagement is governed under CMMI Level 5 processes with full audit documentation.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="egov-build-grid">
        <article class="egov-build-card">
          <span class="egov-build-ic" aria-hidden="true"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.9" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="17 1 21 5 17 9"/><path d="M3 11V9a4 4 0 0 1 4-4h14"/><polyline points="7 23 3 19 7 15"/><path d="M21 13v2a4 4 0 0 1-4 4H3"/></svg></span>
          <h3>Parallel-Run Zero-Downtime Migration</h3>
          <p>Old system stays live while the new one is built, tested, and validated alongside it — no citizen service disruption at any point.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="egov-build-card">
          <span class="egov-build-ic" aria-hidden="true"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.9" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><ellipse cx="12" cy="5" rx="9" ry="3"/><path d="M3 5v14a9 3 0 0 0 18 0V5"/><path d="M3 12a9 3 0 0 0 18 0"/></svg></span>
          <h3>Legacy Database Modernisation</h3>
          <p>Oracle, MS Access, FoxPro, and siloed databases migrated to modern interoperable stacks — with 100% data integrity validation.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="egov-build-card">
          <span class="egov-build-ic" aria-hidden="true"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.9" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><rect x="5" y="2" width="14" height="20" rx="2"/><line x1="12" y1="18" x2="12.01" y2="18"/></svg></span>
          <h3>Desktop-to-Web &amp; Mobile</h3>
          <p>Legacy Windows applications rebuilt as GIGW 3.0 compliant, WCAG 2.1 AA accessible, mobile-first platforms.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="egov-build-card">
          <span class="egov-build-ic" aria-hidden="true"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.9" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M12 22v-5"/><path d="M9 8V2"/><path d="M15 8V2"/><path d="M18 8v4a6 6 0 0 1-12 0V8z"/></svg></span>
          <h3>India Stack &amp; eOffice Retrofitting</h3>
          <p>API layer added to legacy systems enabling Aadhaar, DigiLocker, UPI, and eOffice integration without full redevelopment.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="egov-build-card">
          <span class="egov-build-ic" aria-hidden="true"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.9" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M18 10h-1.26A8 8 0 1 0 9 20h9a5 5 0 0 0 0-10z"/></svg></span>
          <h3>MeghRaj GI Cloud Migration</h3>
          <p>On-premise legacy systems migrated to NIC National Data Centres or MeghRaj — sovereign, DPDP Act 2023 compliant.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="egov-build-card">
          <span class="egov-build-ic" aria-hidden="true"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.9" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M9 11l3 3L22 4"/><path d="M21 12v7a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H5a2 2 0 0 1-2-2V5a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h11"/></svg></span>
          <h3>STQC-Aligned Validation</h3>
          <p>End-to-end testing, UAT, VAPT assessment, and data integrity verification before final cutover — nothing goes live unvalidated.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Certifications -->
  <section class="egov-certs">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="sect-head">
        <span class="egov-eyebrow">Government &amp; Public Sector</span>
        <h2 class="egov-h2">Certifications</h2>
      </div>
      <!-- TODO-WG: confirm the exact list of held certifications; replace any seal below with the real certificate. -->
      <div class="cert-seals-row">
        <div class="cert-seal-card"><div class="cert-seal-img-wrap"><img class="cert-seal-img" src="/images/credentials/cmmi-l5.png" alt="CMMI Level 5 certified" loading="lazy" /></div><div class="cert-seal-card-name">CMMI Level 5</div></div>
        <div class="cert-seal-card"><div class="cert-seal-img-wrap"><img class="cert-seal-img" src="/images/credentials/iso-27001-2022.png" alt="ISO 27001:2022 certified" loading="lazy" /></div><div class="cert-seal-card-name">Information Security</div></div>
        <div class="cert-seal-card"><div class="cert-seal-img-wrap"><img class="cert-seal-img" src="/images/credentials/iso-9001-2015.png" alt="ISO 9001:2015 certified" loading="lazy" /></div><div class="cert-seal-card-name">Quality Management</div></div>
        <div class="cert-seal-card"><div class="cert-seal-img-wrap"><img class="cert-seal-img" src="/images/credentials/iso-20000-2018.png" alt="ISO 20000:2018 certified" loading="lazy" /></div><div class="cert-seal-card-name">IT Service Management</div></div>
        <div class="cert-seal-card"><div class="cert-seal-img-wrap"><img class="cert-seal-img" src="/images/logos/gov/Start up logo.svg" alt="DPIIT — Startup India recognised" loading="lazy" onerror="this.style.display='none'; this.parentNode.classList.add('reg-card-logo--fallback'); this.parentNode.setAttribute('aria-hidden','true'); this.parentNode.textContent='DPIIT';" /></div><div class="cert-seal-card-name">Startup India / DPIIT</div></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ -->
  <section class="egov-faq">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="sect-head">

        <h2 class="egov-h2">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      </div>
      <!-- TODO-WG: verify each Q&A pairing and all compliance/client claims (ISO version, certifications, named bodies) before publishing. -->
      <div class="faq-wrap">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">How does Webority migrate live government systems without disrupting citizen services?</button>
          <div class="faq-a"><p>Legacy system modernisation for government is the structured process of upgrading outdated government IT — old codebases, siloed databases, desktop applications — to modern, interoperable platforms without disrupting live citizen services. It must comply with NIC technical architecture standards, GIGW 3.0, DPDP Act 2023, and enable India Stack integration. Webority delivers this through a four-phase Analyse → Isolate → Migrate → Validate methodology with CMMI Level 5 process governance and STQC-aligned testing.</p></div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">How does Webority ensure zero downtime during government system migration?</button>
          <div class="faq-a"><p>Webority uses parallel-run architecture during all government legacy migrations — the existing system remains live and continues to serve citizens while the modernised version is built, tested, and validated alongside it. Data is synchronised in real-time during the transition window. Cutover is only authorised after full UAT, STQC-aligned testing, VAPT security assessment, and data integrity validation are complete. This approach has been refined through 13+ years of government IT delivery since 2012.</p></div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">How is data integrity guaranteed during government database migrations?</button>
          <div class="faq-a"><p>All legacy modernisation projects delivered by Webority are architected for compatibility with NIC National Data Centre infrastructure and MeghRaj GI Cloud — the Government of India’s sovereign cloud platform. This ensures modernised systems meet GoI data sovereignty requirements, align with DPDP Act 2023 data localisation obligations, and integrate with national digital infrastructure including eOffice, DigiLocker, Aadhaar, and UPI.</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA strip -->
  <section class="egov-cta">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Modernising a legacy government system?</h2>
      <p>Tell us what runs today and what it must connect to — we’ll plan a migration that never takes the service offline.</p>
      <a asp-page="/Contact" class="btn btn-primary btn-glow btn-md"><span class="btn-glow-label">Contact Us</span><svg class="btn-glow-arrow" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M5 12h14"/><path d="M13 6l6 6-6 6"/></svg></a>
    </div>
  </section>

@section HeadStyles {
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="~/css/pages/service-legacy.css" />
